  • Smarter smartwatch: CZ Smart YouQ a proprietary wellness app built using research by NASA Ames Center and AI Models with IBM Watson Studio. YouQ helps wearers maximize their daily potential by learning the wearer’s unique Chronotype and daily rhythms. YouQ computes HR, SP02, fitness activity, sleep, alert scores to offer the consumer 24-hour forecast of alertness. Aggregating data will enable CZ Smart YouQ to cater to wearers personally allowing them to understand their body's rhythms.
  • Self-care advisor: YouQ uses a gamified Alert Monitor, based on NASA’s PVT+. CZ Smart YouQ uses Alert Monitor scores and sleep data to identify the wearer’s Chronotype, a morning go-getter, steady achiever, high-energy hustler?. YouQ helps you stay on track with an Hourly Power Score, an indicator of your cognitive and physical energy at a particular moment. Power Fixes will mitigate fatigue and improve alertness so you can optimize the day. Napuccino or liquid energy in your future
  • Preloaded: Wear OS by Google *compatible with iPhone and Android. Applications available via Play Store include CZ Smart YouQ App, Google Fit, Strava, Spotify, YouTube Music, Amazon Alexa. Features 24+ hour battery life (varies based on usage) achieves a full charge in just 40-minutes. Connections Bluetooth, Wi-Fi, GPS, and NFC. Sensors Gyroscope, altimeter, barometer, accelerometer, heart rate sensor, SP02, ambient light sensor, track activity, heart rate, cardio fitness, steps, sleep
  • Personalization, notifications, and more: The uniquely designed CZ Smart dials give hundreds of options to fully customize your watch face and receive the information you find most important. Stay focused all day while getting notifications on your watch for incoming calls, texts, emails and calendar notifications. The built-in speaker enables you to conveniently answer a call from your smartwatch. With Amazon Alexa built-in, CZ Smart makes it easy to tackle your daily tasks and organization.
  • Citizen Connected works with phones running on the latest version of Android (excluding Go Edition and phones without Google Play Store) or iOS, 24+ hour battery life, Qualcomm 4100+ chipset

    • Brian G.
      3.0 out of 5 starsVerified Purchase
      Beautiful watch, App is clunky
      Reviewed in the United States on March 26, 2025
      Color: Silver
      This is a beautiful watch, and is comfortable to wear. However, the app software and connectivity with this watch is incredibly clunky to, say the least. With other smartwatches (including the cheap ones), the connectivity is seamless. You can connect to a new phone or... See more
      This is a beautiful watch, and is comfortable to wear. However, the app software and connectivity with this watch is incredibly clunky to, say the least. With other smartwatches (including the cheap ones), the connectivity is seamless. You can connect to a new phone or device quickly and efficiently, but not with this watch. Anytime you want connect to a new device, you have to factory reset the watch and have to start over. If there is a way to switch devices where I don't have I do that, I couldn't find it, and I scoured through the watch and the app, to no avail. All the custom faces and specific options are just gone. Then, after the reset, it takes the app a bit to even get the options back that it had before resetting. As I said, it's clunky and not nearly up to the same level as other smartwatch platforms. My recommendation for Citizen is to put some work into your app and save account data so transitioning your watch from device to device isn't such a pain. When I see the name Citizen on a watch, I expect the highest quality, precision, style, and functionality. Let's face it, their Ecodrive watches are sweet! However, this experience with their smartwatch app/software makes it feel like they rushed this out of product testing without it fully being ready to actually go. I know the new trend seems to be going to smartwatches instead of the traditional ones, but if you're going to be competitive in this particular market, you need to have an app that'll compete too.

      So grading wise:
      Style: A+

      Battery life: C- (have to charge every night.. not the biggest deal but other smartwatches can last significantly longer aka days to weeks)

      App/software: F

      Functionality once you get through the app woes: A- to B+

      I believe in Citizen and I know they can improve on this product as time goes on. I wouldn't say "buyer beware" but maybe wait until this one is on sale.

    • D. A. B.
      2.0 out of 5 starsVerified Purchase
      Not What I Would Expect From Citizen
      Reviewed in the United States on December 20, 2024
      Color: Black
      I really wanted this watch to work for me. I read all the negative reviews but when this watch was discounted to $117 on Amazon, I couldn't pass up trying it out. In my watch collection, I have 14 Citizen watches. I always recommend Citizen watches to my... See more
      I really wanted this watch to work for me. I read all the negative reviews but when this watch was discounted to $117 on Amazon, I couldn't pass up trying it out.

      In my watch collection, I have 14 Citizen watches. I always recommend Citizen watches to my friends and family. As a rule, Citizen watches are durable, accurate and a great value for the price. This watch is the exception to that rule.

      The build quality was good and the case design was similar to one of the conventional watches in my collection. The screen was very good and the menus/controls were user friendly for the most part. From there, I was disappointed.

      Initially I had trouble pairing it to my iPhone (actually I had trouble keeping it paired to my iPhone). After a few hours of unsuccessful tweaking I did a factory reset on the watch and started over. Everything paired up and worked fine after starting over after the watch was reset. The Citizen Connect app worked great.

      The first big issue with this watch is the battery life. Only one day of use did I get close to 24 hours of run time. All other days gave me a battery life of 8 to 12 hours on average. I had one day where it needed to recharged after only 4 hours!

      The second issue for me was the step count accuracy. I use a Fitbit. This watch and the Fitbit were never close. On days that my Fitbit said I had 10,000 steps, the watch would show 6,000 to 7,000 steps. That is a huge difference that I could not live with. I looked up discussions on-line about the watch's accuracy and found a site where Citizen claimed they used sophisticated algorithms for tracking so that the watch would only count true steps and not count arm/wrist movements as steps. I found that to not be true. I could sit in a chair and shake my wrist or move my arm and see the step count on the watch display increase with each movement. I also noticed that when walking with my hands in my coat pockets or when pushing a stroller, no steps were detected or counted.

      Like I said, I really wanted this watch to work for me. I used it for six days and gave it several "second chances" but it never got any better. I do find it hard to believe that Citizen has not addressed the issues noted in this and other reviews. The watch has been on the market for a few years and it is still listed for purchase on the Citizen website so I am puzzled why the watch isn't better than it is.

      Believe all the negative reviews and save your money on purchasing this watch. I'm sending this one back.

      If you are looking for a good conventional watch (not a smart watch), I still recommend Citizen watches.

    • C. McDannold
      1.0 out of 5 starsVerified Purchase
      I know why Fossil dropped smartwatches
      Reviewed in the United States on May 14, 2024
      Color: Blue
      This watch says Citizen, but it is a Fossil through and through. (Fossil Gen 6, to be specific) This watch is incredibly frustrating to use. Input lag is horrible, and heaven forbid if you’re downloading something when you want to interact with the watch. It literally... See more
      This watch says Citizen, but it is a Fossil through and through. (Fossil Gen 6, to be specific) This watch is incredibly frustrating to use. Input lag is horrible, and heaven forbid if you’re downloading something when you want to interact with the watch. It literally freezes up. Downloads are painfully slow, and 50% of the time, remote installs via Play Store do not process on the watch. I’ve yet to see more than 5 hours of battery life before the watch switches to extended mode.

      Watch faces are gimped because they have “curated” your customization options. So the background color and other colors change in unison – you have no granularity. No dark blue with white text for you. Citizen has decided that is no “on brand” apparently.

      Calendar does not sync with anything, regardless of the setup process. So, the built-in calendar apps are useless. Google pay no longer exists, so it updated to Google Wallet. This is fine, but when you try to configure a default payment, it wants to use Google Pay through Google Wallet.

      This really isn’t rocket science. If you’re going to go “all-in” with Wear OS, then do that. This hybrid environment masquerading as Wear OS is broken and inefficient. For what this device costs, the experience should be on par with a Galaxy Watch or an Apple Watch. This isn’t TicWatch or Amazfit – people are willing to make allowances for user experience at their prices, though, to be fair, they “get it” when it comes to UX, generally speaking.

      Bottom line, if you’re looking for a smartwatch in a more traditional watch casing, this isn’t it.
